<paragraph blockId="11.[160,1156,1360,1661]" pageId="11" pageNumber="876">
Note: 
<bibRefCitation author="Kielland J" box="[231,395,1360,1384]" pageId="11" pageNumber="876" refId="ref22372" refString="Kielland J. 1990. Butterflies of Tanzania. Melbourne: Hill House." type="book" year="1990">Kielland (1990</bibRefCitation>
, p. 83, as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Trimen" authorityYear="1873" box="[523,746,1360,1384]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Henotesia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="876" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="perspicua">
<emphasis box="[523,746,1360,1384]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="876">Henotesia perspicua</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) considered this to be a polytypic species, with 
<emphasis box="[313,318,1395,1419]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="876">‘</emphasis>
a distinct race in 
<collectingCountry box="[515,632,1395,1419]" name="Cameroon" pageId="11" pageNumber="876">Cameroun</collectingCountry>
<emphasis box="[632,638,1395,1419]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="876">’</emphasis>
, named in a later publication (
<bibRefCitation author="Kielland J" box="[988,1142,1395,1419]" pageId="11" pageNumber="876" pagination="235 - 273" refId="ref22405" refString="Kielland J. 1994. A revision of the genus Henotesia (excluding Madagascar and other Indian Ocean eislands) (Lepidoptera Satyridae). Lambillionea. 94: 235 - 273." type="journal article" year="1994">Kielland 1994</bibRefCitation>
). Only treated as monotypic by 
<bibRefCitation author="Ackery PR &amp; Smith CR &amp; Vane-Wright RI" box="[510,722,1429,1453]" pageId="11" pageNumber="876" refId="ref20969" refString="Ackery PR, Smith CR, Vane-Wright RI, editors. 1995. Carcasson ' s African Butterflies: an annotated catalogue of the Papilionoidea and Hesperioidea of the Afrotropical Region. East Melbourne: CSIRO." type="book" year="1995">Ackery et al. (1995</bibRefCitation>
, as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Trimen" authorityYear="1873" box="[768,989,1429,1453]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Henotesia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="876" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="perspicua">
<emphasis box="[768,989,1429,1453]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="876">Henotesia perspicua</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), and listed as without representation in 
<collectingCountry box="[463,582,1464,1488]" name="Cameroon" pageId="11" pageNumber="876">Cameroon</collectingCountry>
, because Kielland 
<emphasis box="[787,792,1464,1488]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="876">’</emphasis>
s 1994 paper came too late for inclusion. Like many Mycaelsina, this species shows seasonal variation, notably with respect to expression of the border ocelli 
<emphasis box="[630,643,1533,1557]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="876">–</emphasis>
for which 
<bibRefCitation author="Riley ND" box="[763,886,1533,1557]" pageId="11" pageNumber="876" refId="ref23244" refString="Riley ND. 1925. Henotesia perspicua Trimen [Lep. Satyridae] and its seasonal forms. T Entomol Soc Lond. 1925: xix - xxi." type="journal volume" year="1925">Riley (1925</bibRefCitation>
, as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Trimen" authorityYear="1873" box="[929,1148,1533,1557]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Henotesia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="876" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="perspicua">
<emphasis box="[929,1148,1533,1557]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="876">Henotesia perspicua</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) still offers a useful summary in relation to two closely related species, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Butler, 1877)" baseAuthorityName="Butler" baseAuthorityYear="1877" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Heteropsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="876" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="simonsii">
<emphasis box="[948,1155,1568,1592]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="876">Heteropsis simonsii</emphasis>
(Butler, 1877)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Karsch, 1894)" baseAuthorityName="Karsch" baseAuthorityYear="1894" box="[378,745,1603,1627]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Heteropsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="876" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="teratia">
<emphasis box="[378,572,1603,1627]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="876">Heteropsis teratia</emphasis>
(Karsch, 1894)
</taxonomicName>
, both of which occur elsewhere in 
<collectingCountry box="[160,262,1637,1661]" name="Tanzania" pageId="11" pageNumber="876">Tanzania</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[160,1156,141,548]" box="[160,252,141,167]" pageId="12" pageNumber="877">
